There can be several reasons why the background color is not being updated in Windows 10. Here are a few possible solutions that you can try:

1. Check the theme settings: It is possible that the color settings in Windows 10 are overriding the background color that you are specifying for the ComboBox. Check the color scheme/theme settings in Windows 10 and make sure that they are not preventing the background color from being set.

2. Check the AccentColor settings: Windows 10 has an accent color setting that affects the color of some UI elements, such as the ComboBox dropdown arrow. If the accent color is white, it could be preventing the background color of the ComboBox from being visible. You can try changing the accent color to a different color and see if that helps.

3. Check the HighContrast settings: If the High Contrast setting is enabled in Windows 10, it may also prevent the background color of the ComboBox from being visible. You can try disabling the High Contrast setting and see if that helps.

4. Try setting the Background property of the ComboBox: Instead of using the ColorearCombobox method to set the background color of the ComboBox, you can try setting the Background property of the ComboBox directly in the ComboBox_SelectionChanged event handler. For example:

```
private void ComboBoxH1_SelectionChanged(object sender, SelectionChangedEventArgs e)
{
    ComboBox comboBox = sender as ComboBox;
    comboBox.Background = Brushes.Blue; // set the background color
}
```

